# Matt Pocock engineering workflow

This repo uses [mattpocock/skills](https://github.com/mattpocock/skills). Skills live in `.agents/skills/`. Project wiring is in root `AGENTS.md` and `docs/agents/`.

## Before coding (non-trivial work)

1. Read `CONTEXT-MAP.md` and the relevant `HuLa/CONTEXT.md` or `HuLa-Server/CONTEXT.md`.
2. Check `docs/adr/` for decisions in the area you will touch.
3. Prefer **`grill-with-docs`** (or **`grill-me`**) to align scope before implementation — one question at a time when grilling.

## While coding

- **`tdd`**: vertical slices only (one failing test → make it pass → refactor). Client tests: `pnpm test:run` in `HuLa/`. Server: module-appropriate Maven/Gradle tests.
- **`diagnose`**: bugs — reproduce, minimise, hypothesise, instrument, fix, regression test.
- **`zoom-out`**: when entering unfamiliar modules, explain system context first.

## Issues and planning

- Tracker: GitHub `solmyr138-sol/HuLa` via `gh` — see `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`.
- Triage labels: `docs/agents/triage-labels.md`.
- **`to-prd`** / **`to-issues`** for breaking work into issues; **`triage`** for incoming tickets.

## Vocabulary

Use terms from the active `CONTEXT.md`. Do not invent synonyms listed under _Avoid_.

## HuLa client extras

When editing only `HuLa/`, also follow `HuLa/AGENTS.md` and the `hula-skill` scope routing (frontend / backend / fullstack / build-release).
